                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>(C.) In nomine sanctae et individuae trinitatis. <persName
                            key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/7">Otto</persName> divina favente
                        clementia <rs key="#Emperor/king">imperator</rs> augustus. Quia imperialis
                        magnificentia pia et larga erga dei cultores aecclesiarum dei recuperatrix
                        et restauratrix esse debet, ut id agendo praemium mereatur consequi
                        sempiternum: idcirco omnium fidelium sanctae dei ecclesiae nostrorumque
                        praesentium ac futurorum devotio noverit, qualiter nos consultu ac
                        interventu <persName key="#Intercessory #Bishops #fidelisOf"><name
                                ref="Helmpratus">Helmprati</name></persName> venerabilis <rs
                            key="#Bishops">episcopi</rs> nostrique <rs key="#fidelisOf">fidelis</rs>
                        aliquantam <rs key="#Landed_possessions">terram</rs> quam bone memoriae
                            <persName key="#Bishops"><name ref="Petrus">Petrus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">episcopus</rs> ad utilitatem <rs key="#Canons"
                            >canonicorum</rs> in <rs key="#Churches">ecclesia</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis #Villas #Curtes #Landed_possessions #Forests #Gualdi #Size #Wine #Agricultural_workers #Periodic_markets #Pagus #Census #Tuitio/bannum/mundeburdium #Priests #Archdeacons #Other_clerics #Canons"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1402">sancti Donati confessoris et martiris
                            Christi</orgName> ibi pro tempore servientium deo distribuit ibi et
                        antecessores nostri imperatores et reges postea confirmaverunt et suo
                        proprio <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Inflow #Gift #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >dono</rs> concesserunt, videlicet <rs key="#Wine">vineam</rs> unam ad
                            <placeName
                            key="#Wine #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Pinum</placeName> cum <rs key="#Landed_possessions">campo</rs> ibi
                        prope similiter ad Pinum nominante et <rs key="#Landed_possessions">campum
                            alterum qui dicitur Protosale</rs> nec non <rs key="#Curtes"
                            >corticellam</rs> unam que dicitur ad <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/1431"><placeName
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >Clane</placeName></geogName> cum sua pertinentia et alia <rs
                            key="#Curtes">corticella</rs> que vocatur <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/1432"><placeName
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >Moiona</placeName></geogName> sub integritate, sicut discernitur in
                        scripto ad iam nominato Petro episcopo facto, <rs key="#Churches"
                            >ecclesiam</rs> quoque <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1427">sancti Petri in castello</orgName> quam
                        dive memoriae <persName ref="#people/9">Lotharius</persName> pro remedio
                        anime suae canonicos ibi servientes habere concessit, nec non et <rs
                            key="#Villas">villas</rs> tres quarum una nominatur <geogName
                            key="#Villas #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/1433"><placeName
                                key="#Villas #Fiscal_property #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >Dorna</placeName></geogName>, altera <geogName
                            key="#Villas #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/1434"><placeName
                                key="#Villas #Fiscal_property #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >Pliga</placeName></geogName>, tertia <geogName
                            key="#Villas #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/1435"><placeName
                                key="#Villas #Fiscal_property #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >Spegia</placeName></geogName>, quas praedictus Lotharius canonicis
                        confirmavit, <rs key="#Periodic_markets">mercatum</rs> insuper unum quod
                        celebratur in missa sancti Hilariani, <rs key="#Curtes">curtem</rs> etiam
                        qui vocatur <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/1436"><placeName
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >Caminina</placeName></geogName> et est in <placeName
                            ref="#places/1803">castro Felicitatis</placeName> cum <rs
                            key="#Churches">ecclesia</rs> in honore <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            >sancti Andree</orgName> aedificata cum omni sua pertinentia quam
                        praefatus imperator canonicis concessit, <rs key="#Landed_possessions"
                            >campum insuper unum qui vocatur Piscinule</rs> et consistit in <rs
                            key="#Pagus">pago</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Pagus" ref="#places/505">Aritinense</placeName> cum omnibus
                        suis appenditiis, ut praetaxatus imperator eis concessit, <rs key="#Curtes"
                            >curtem</rs> namque que vocatur <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/1437"><placeName
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >Colonaria</placeName></geogName> cum omni sua pertinentia, per hoc
                        nostrum imperiale praeceptum canonicis qui nunc ibi serviunt, <persName
                            key="#Archdeacons #Canons"><name ref="Wilielmus"
                            >Vuillehelmo</name></persName> scilicet <rs key="#Archdeacons"
                            >archidiacono</rs> et <persName key="#Priests #Canons"><name
                                ref="Berardus">Berahardo</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Priests">presbitero</rs> et primicerio, <persName
                            key="#Other_clerics #Canons"><name ref="Martinus"
                            >Martino</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Other_clerics">clerico</rs> et custodem sancti Donati, <persName
                            key="#Canons"><name ref="Sigitius">Sigizonem</name></persName> scole
                        cantorem, <persName key="#Priests #Canons"><name ref="Michael"
                                >Michahel</name></persName> presbitero, <persName
                            key="#Priests #Canons"><name ref="Atto">Ato</name></persName>
                        presbitero, <persName key="#Priests #Canons"><name ref="Winizo"
                                >Uuinizoni</name></persName> presbitero, <persName
                            key="#Priests #Canons"><name ref="Iohannes">Iohanni</name></persName>
                        presbitero, <persName key="#Priests #Canons"><name ref="Gherardus"
                                >Girardo</name></persName> presbitero, <persName
                            key="#Priests #Canons"><name ref="Bertus">Berto</name></persName>
                        presbitero, <persName key="#Priests #Canons"><name ref="Iudo"
                            >Iudoni</name></persName> presbitero, <persName key="#Bishops #Canons"
                                ><name ref="Leo">Leoni</name></persName> presbitero et reliquis qui
                        ibi in praesenti serviunt eorumque successoribus qui futuris temporibus qui
                        ibi servierint, restituimus confirmamus pleniterque corroboramus etiam
                        praedicti loci canonicis <rs key="#Curtes">curticellam</rs> unam quam dive
                        memoriae noster <rs key="#grandparentOf">avus</rs>
                        <persName key="#Emperor/king #grandparentOf" ref="#people/173"
                            >Otto</persName>
                        <rs key="#Emperor/king">imperator</rs> eis concessit, que coniacet in
                        avocabulo <placeName
                            key="#Curtes #Forests #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Toppo</placeName> una cum ipsa <rs key="#Forests">silva que dicitur
                            Arbororo</rs> et una cum omni pertinentia sua et cum ipsa <rs
                            key="#Gualdi">waldemannia</rs> que coniacet in <placeName
                            key="#Gualdi #Fiscal_property #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Uico</placeName> et in <placeName
                            key="#Gualdi #Fiscal_property #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Polliciano</placeName> et in <placeName
                            key="#Gualdi #Fiscal_property #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Petiano</placeName> et per illorum vocabula, et <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions">campum unum qui dicitur Longoria</rs>
                        coniacentem prope <placeName
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Perulascio</placeName> qui capere videtur <rs key="#Size">modia
                            viginti</rs>, ita videlicet ut nec rector huiusdem sedis nec cuiuslibet
                        potestatis persona de praefatis rebus vel de eorum pertinentiis seu de his
                        que divina pietas inibi agere voluerit illis aliquam inferre praesumet
                        contrarietatem vel diminorationem ullam ingerere adtemptet. Confirmamus eis
                        scilicet <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Inflow #Gift #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >terram</rs> quam <persName key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/79"
                            >Ugo</persName>
                        <rs key="#Emperor/king">rex</rs> de sua proprietate eisdem concessit
                        canonicis, id est <rs key="#Landed_possessions">campum unum de Piunta</rs>
                        et <rs key="#Landed_possessions">campum de Gratigata</rs>, ut [i]llis abque
                        aliqua minoratione aut cuiuslibet potestatis contrarietate perhennis
                        perseveret temporibus. Statuimus quoque ut sit ipsa canonica cum canonicis
                        ipsius loci sub magisterio et regimine Uuillehelmi archidiaconi et Berahardi
                        archipresbiteri eorumque successorum, facientes pari voto communique
                        consensu de frugibus et redditibus quod in ipsa canonica annualiter dominus
                        dederit seu de helemosinis absolute et libere, quod canonici facere debent,
                        abque ullius contradictione vel molestatione. Quia Tuscis consuetudo est ut,
                        accepto ab ecclesia <rs key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis">libello</rs>,
                        in contumaciam convertantur contra ecclesiam, ita ut vix aut constitutum
                        reddant <rs key="#Census">censum</rs>, praecipimus quoque ut his que omnibus
                        iubemus ut non episcopus vel canonicus libellum aut aliquod scriptum alicui
                        homini faciant, nisi <rs key="#Agricultural_workers">laboratoribus</rs> qui
                        fructum terre ecclesiae et canonicis ipsius loci reddant sine molestia vel
                        contradictione aliqua. Praecipimus quoque ut in ipsa canonica nulla deinceps
                        adiciatur persona absque communi consensu, ne propter hoc aliqua inter illos
                        oriatur discordia. Pro maiori quoque illorum securitate praecipimus illos
                        cum omnibus illorum mobilibus et inmobilibus rebus illis iuste et legaliter
                        pertinentibus sub nostrae <rs key="#Tuitio/bannum/mundeburdium">tuitionis
                            mundiburdio</rs>, quatenus securae vivere deoque servire et pro nobis
                        statuque regni nostri remedioque anime nostrae orare illis iugiter delectet.
                        Si quis igitur nostrae huius confirmationis praecepti et mundiburdii
                        violator aut contradictor extiterit, sciat se compositurum <rs
                            key="#Penalty">auri optimi libras centum</rs>, <rs key="#Camera_regis"
                            >medietatem camere nostrae</rs> et <rs
                            key="#Camera_of_other_public_authorities">medietate praefatis canonicis
                            qui in ecclesia beati Donati pro tempore serviunt</rs>. Quod ut verius
                        credatur diligentiusque ab omnibus observetur, manu propria roborantes
                        nostro sigillo subter annotari iussimus.Signum domni Ottonis invictissimi
                        (M.) imperatoris augusti. <persName key="#Chancellor"><name ref="Eribertus"
                                >Heribertus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Chancellor">cancellarius</rs> vice <persName
                            key="#Archchancellor #Bishops"><name ref="Petrus"
                            >Petri</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">episcopi</rs> et <rs key="#Archchancellor"
                            >archicancellarii</rs> notavi. (SI. D.) Data IIII. id. iul. anno
                        dominice incarnationis DCCCCXCVI, indictione VIIII, anno vero tertii Ottonis
                        regnantis XIII, imperii autem primo; actum in ecclesia sancti Donati;
                        feliciter amen.</ab>
                </div>
